Command Line Interface of requs

  Download <<<requs-bin.jar>>> and run it:

---
java -jar requs-bin.jar [-?v] <report>+ < <input-file>
---

  Every <<<\<report\>>>> is formatted as:

---
<name>:<arg1>[=<value1>][,<arg2>[=<value2>]...]
---

  For example:

---
java -jar requs-bin.jar errors:max=50,unique metrics < srs.txt
---

  This request parses provided <<<srs.txt>>> file and
  produces an XML output, where <<<errors>>> and <<<metrics>>>
  reporters inject their data:

+--
<?xml version="1.0">
<requs xmlns="http://requs.org/"
  xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
  xsi:schemaLocation="http://requs.org/ http://requs.org/requs.xsd>
  <errors>
    <report max="50" unique="true">
      <errors>
        <error line="15">Invalid syntax of entity</error>
        <error line="54">Missed argument</error>
      </errors>
    </report>
  </errors>
  <metrics>
    <report>
      <version>0.3-SNAPSHOT</version>
      <ambiguity>0.865</ambiguity>
    </report>
  </metrics>
</requs>
+--
